criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  No history of lung disease;

          -  Forced vital capacity (FVC) or forced expiratory volume in the first second (FEV1)
             higher or equal to 80% from predicted values (Pereira et al., 1992),

          -  No history of smoking;

          -  Without respiratory or cardiovascular disease;

          -  Ability to understand verbal commands;

          -  Willing to provide signed consent to participate in this study.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Pregnant;

          -  Were unable to tolerate NIV (Metha and Hill, 2001).
